comments.body:
@mheon wrt:
> running with -a causes podman to stay alive until the container dies, which is suitable for a systemd simple unit

Does this running alive differ from what we had with docker daemon required to be alive, in the past, when managing systemd units via that daemon? That scenario brings troubles when the daemon restarts, IIRC. So if that staying alive podman dies unexpectedly, what happens to the "orphaned" container launched via that unit file?
